ional weavers and dyers.				 																																	 April 2 - 4 at 1/57B Dover Place; 2 pm - 7 pm: Gharoyas exhibition-cum-sale of saris and salwars.				 																																	 April 3 at Rakhi Sangha, opp. Chetla Park; 11 am - 8 pm: An exhibition cum fete organised by Inner Wheel Club of South Calcutta.				 																																	 Till April 3 at Sravasti, 14/97 Golf Club Road, beside RCGC; 1.30 pm - 8.30 pm: KeyaChaitali displays her creations of T shirts, short kurtas, punjabis, saradin, salwar suits, lungi-tops, mekhla, blouse pieces, costume jewellery, sarees and her unique Podyo-Poshak.				 																																	 Till April 3 at Weavers Studio, 5/1 Anil Moitra Road, Ballygunge Place; 10 am - 6 pm: Collections by Kilol, Creative Bee, Prasiddhi; Vimor - revival amp; reproduction of Kalakshetra saris; Khoj maheswari hand-block prints on saris by Kavita Sanghi; and Weavers Studio chikankari, linen, organzas, georgettes, textured cotton, Benarasi summer wedding saris.				 																																	 Till April 15 at Sampas Boutique, 42 Circus Avenue; 10 am - 8 pm: Wonder weaves from Assam silk and muga sarees and Mekhla chaddars.
